column9: We offer unmatched expertise in computer science education. Students aged 8-18 can engage in fun projects while becoming expert coders. We offer a variety of computer science programs to enhance your child's STEM education. We offer camps and workshops, and we offer K-12 after-school programs at many schools throughout California and we are excited to be expanding into Massachusetts! With the help of professionally trained instructors augmented by high school and college mentors, your child can learn to code through our project-based curriculum.

The Charles M. Schulz Museum and Research Center was designed to reflect the modest, low key, and comfortable personality and style of the internationally-famous cartoonist and creator of the Peanut Gang. The Schulz Museum offers classes in computer animation, cartooning, character design, and other arts throughout the year for children and adults. Classes are taught by professionals focusing on their area of expertise. Students of all skill levels are welcome.

column9: MakersFactory is a 3D learning company that offers classes, products and services to educate students, teachers and communities in 21st century skills. As a company, we strive to offer a positive, educational and fun experience for all of our attendees.  We offer afterschool clubs, classes, and holiday camps for ages 9 and up.

column9: We take pride in providing individual attention to students and to serving the community's changing needs. Course formats include one-day workshops, weekend programs, seminars, intensive short courses and courses that meet once a week during the 10-week academic quarter. Many classes are offered at night and on weekends to accommodate busy schedules. We offer many youth classes, from technology to archeology to language for grades 3 through 8.
